# Phase 35.3 · Frontend Dashboard / UI Polish

Repository: `cvsz/zdash`

Execution profile: DeepSeek V4 Flash Free / fast free coding model.

Goal:
Polish the zDash frontend dashboard and UI/UX for final release readiness while preserving existing backend contracts and all safety messaging.

Do not redesign the whole app. Do not add new dependencies unless absolutely required. Use existing components and patterns.

---

## Safety invariants

- Do not add any live trading button.
- Do not hide dry-run or simulation-only labels.
- Trading and AI Trader screens must say simulation-only / dry-run / not financial advice.
- Billing pages must show mock provider state when using mock billing.
- Marketplace must show plugin safety notes and review requirements.
- Enterprise export with secrets must require typed confirmation.
- Settings must never show secret values.
- Do not change backend contracts unless a frontend test proves the contract is broken.
- Do not commit `.env`, local caches, node_modules, dist, or Codex run artifacts.

---

## Inspect first

Inspect only frontend files needed for UI polish:

```text
frontend/src/App.tsx
frontend/src/api/
frontend/src/components/common/
frontend/src/components/layout/
frontend/src/components/trading/
frontend/src/components/billing/
frontend/src/components/marketplace/
frontend/src/components/enterprise/
frontend/src/pages/
frontend/src/tests/
frontend/package.json
frontend/tsconfig*.json
```

Create an inspection summary:

```text
- routes checked
- dashboard pages checked
- duplicate imports found
- missing loading states
- missing empty states
- missing error states
- safety-label gaps
- test/build risks
```

---

## Required UI areas

### App routing

Verify routes render and are reachable:

```text
/
/login
/risk
/scheduler
/content
/xau
/billing
/usage
/marketplace
/enterprise
/onboarding
/admin
/workspace
```

Do not remove existing routes.

### Layout

Verify:

- Sidebar links match available routes.
- Topbar renders tenant branding when available.
- Mobile/responsive layout does not break core pages.
- Loading/fallback UI is readable.

### Dashboard

Verify:

- core system cards render
- quota warnings show when relevant
- fallback/mock banners are visible
- safety state is clearly labelled
- no raw backend errors are dumped without user-friendly context

### XAU / Trading / AI Trader

Verify:

- dry-run banner is visible
- Guardian/risk wording is visible
- AI Trader card shows strategy selector
- AI Trader card shows simulation-only banner
- generated direction/confidence/validation/execution states render
- compare table works
- paper trade button says dry-run only
- no live trading button exists

### Billing / Usage

Verify:

- billing mock provider banner appears
- subscription status appears
- pricing/plan table appears
- invoice table appears
- quota warnings appear at >80%
- exceeded quota banner appears
- payment secrets are never shown

### Marketplace

Verify:

- plugin grid renders
- plugin safety level appears
- install/enable/disable/uninstall actions are clearly dry-run/sandboxed unless explicitly allowed
- installed plugin table renders
- entitlement/quota warning appears where relevant

### Enterprise

Verify:

- license status renders
- branding editor escapes/sanitizes preview content
- export/import panel requires typed confirmation for secrets
- onboarding checklist renders
- customer health score renders
- white-label preview is safe

### Onboarding

Verify:

- steps render
- safety checklist appears
- quick actions are dry-run labelled
- billing/risk/content/trading links are clear

---

## UI/UX improvements allowed

Allowed:

- wording improvements
- duplicate import cleanup
- broken route fixes
- missing fallback/empty/loading/error states
- accessibility labels
- safer button labels
- small component extraction using existing style
- test updates for clear assertions

Not allowed:

- major redesign
- dependency churn
- new state management framework
- backend rewrites
- removing safety banners
- adding live-trading UI
- exposing secrets

---

## Tests

Add or update tests only for critical UI paths changed:

```text
frontend/src/tests/App.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/Dashboard.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/AITrader.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/Billing.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/Usage.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/Marketplace.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/Enterprise.test.tsx
frontend/src/tests/Onboarding.test.tsx
```

Avoid ambiguous Testing Library assertions. If repeated text is expected, use `findAllByText` or scoped queries.

---

## Validation

Targeted first:

```bash
cd frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test -- AITrader.test.tsx Billing.test.tsx Usage.test.tsx Marketplace.test.tsx Enterprise.test.tsx Onboarding.test.tsx
```

Full frontend validation:

```bash
cd frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test
npm run build
```

Full repo fast validation if frontend passes:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
make validate-fast
```

---

## Non-blocking known warnings

These warnings are not blockers if final test summaries pass:

```text
React act(...) warnings in existing hook tests
React Router future flag warnings
intentional ErrorBoundary test Error: fail
```

